cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about benchmarking deep reinforcement learning algorithms in a batch setting, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on the Atari domain, which is a popular benchmark for reinforcement learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses computer vision techniques to process the Atari game images, so cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with control problems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
